Cleaning the Dataset

In [ ]:
# copy of the file
fatalities_conflict_data_copy = fatalities_conflict_data.copy()

# Handle the missing values by dropping the rows with null values
fatalities_conflict_data_copy.dropna(inplace=True, thresh=5)

# Remove the duplicate data by dropping the rows with same values
fatalities_conflict_data_copy.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)

# Standardize the data by replacing the inconsistent values with common ones
fatalities_conflict_data_copy.event_location.replace({"Jerusalem": "Jerusalem District", "Gaza": "Gaza Strip", "West Bank": "West Bank and Gaza"}, inplace=True)
fatalities_conflict_data_copy.event_location_district.replace({"Jerusalem": "Jerusalem District", "Gaza": "Gaza Strip", "West Bank": "West Bank and Gaza"}, inplace=True)
fatalities_conflict_data_copy.event_location_region.replace({"Jerusalem": "Jerusalem District", "Gaza": "Gaza Strip", "West Bank": "West Bank and Gaza"}, inplace=True)

# Remove the unnecessary columns by dropping them
fatalities_conflict_data_copy.drop(["date_of_event","event_location_district","notes"], axis=1, inplace=True)

# Convert the date columns to datetime format
fatalities_conflict_data_copy.date_of_death = pd.to_datetime(fatalities_conflict_data_copy.date_of_death)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns

def demographic_analysis(fatalities_conflict_data_copy):
    # EDA Question 1
    avg_age = fatalities_conflict_data_copy['age'].mean()
    age_distribution = fatalities_conflict_data_copy.groupby('gender')['age'].plot(kind='hist', alpha=0.5, legend=True)
    
    return avg_age, age_distribution

def event_characteristics(fatalities_conflict_data_copy):
    # EDA Question 2
    common_injury = fatalities_conflict_data_copy['type_of_injury'].mode().iloc[0]
    injury_trends = fatalities_conflict_data_copy.groupby('death_year')['type_of_injury'].value_counts().unstack().plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    return common_injury, injury_trends

def geographical_patterns(fatalities_conflict_data_copy):
    # EDA Question 3
    region_freq = fatalities_conflict_data_copy['event_location_region'].value_counts()
    location_injury_corr = pd.crosstab(fatalities_conflict_data_copy['event_location_region'], fatalities_conflict_data_copy['type_of_injury'])
    
    # Visualization: Location Heatmap
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    sns.heatmap(location_injury_corr, annot=True, cmap="YlGnBu")
    plt.title('Location vs. Injury Type')
    plt.show()

    return region_freq

def temporal_trends(fatalities_conflict_data_copy):
    # EDA Question 5
    events_over_years = fatalities_conflict_data_copy.groupby('death_year').size()
    
    # Visualization: Temporal Trends
    events_over_years.plot(kind='line', marker='o')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of death')
    plt.title('Temporal Trends of death')
    plt.show()

    return events_over_years


avg_age, age_distribution = demographic_analysis(fatalities_conflict_data_copy)
common_injury, injury_trends = event_characteristics(fatalities_conflict_data_copy)
region_freq = geographical_patterns(fatalities_conflict_data_copy)
events_over_years = temporal_trends(fatalities_conflict_data_copy)
